We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Instruct the heads of the requisitioning office to give the complete description  and exact unit of measure of the items being requisitioned, indicate the date and PR number and affix his/her signature in the Purchase Request (PR).  Refrain from indicating the brand name of the items  except for replacement of parts of vehicles or equipment;

Instruct the General Services Officer  (GSO) - Designate who is in charge in making canvass of prices to see to it that the Requests for Quotation (RFQ) indicate the complete specification and exact unit of measure of the items being canvassed and avoid indicating the brand name of the items except for replacement of parts of vehicles or equipment.  She should see to it that all the required data in the RFQ, PO, AIR and Driver’s Trip Tickets   such as the number of the document, dates, proper signatures, etc.  are indicated therein; 

Instruct the BAC to see to it that the Abstract of Bids/Canvass and other  documents such as the RFQs,  etc. are properly accomplished; and 

Instruct the Municipal Accountant Designate to be guided by the documentary requirements in the disbursement of funds as embodied in COA Circular 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012 and other issuances.  Likewise, she should not process claims for payment without complete and duly accomplished supporting documents in order to ascertain the validity, propriety and reliability of the transactions and to avoid suspensions in audit.

